{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b22a363d-ace6-4011-a3a0-494b4f668c89","content":"Here's the setup:\n\n**AppShell.xaml**\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<Shell x:Class=\"YourApp.AppShell\"\n       xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n       xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n       xmlns:views=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.Views\"\n       FlyoutBehavior=\"Flyout\">\n\n    <!-- Dashboard — single page, own flyout item -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Dashboard\" Icon=\"dashboard.png\">\n        <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:DashboardPage}\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Products — two tabs -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Products\" Icon=\"products.png\">\n        <Tab Title=\"Active\">\n            <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ActiveProductsPage}\" />\n        </Tab>\n        <Tab Title=\"Archived\">\n            <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ArchivedProductsPage}\" />\n        </Tab>\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Settings -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Settings\" Icon=\"settings.png\">\n        <ShellContent ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:SettingsPage}\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n</Shell>\n```\n\n**AppShell.xaml.cs** — register the detail route:\n```csharp\nnamespace YourApp;\n\npublic partial class AppShell : Shell\n{\n    public AppShell()\n    {\n        InitializeComponent();\n\n        // Register routes for pages not in the visual hierarchy\n        Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(Views.ProductDetailsPage), typeof(Views.ProductDetailsPage));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Navigate to it** from a product list:\n```csharp\nawait Shell.Current.GoToAsync($\"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?id={product.Id}\");\n```\n\nAnd receive the parameter:\n```csharp\n[QueryProperty(nameof(ProductId), \"id\")]\npublic partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage\n{\n    public string ProductId { get; set; }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- `FlyoutItem` creates a flyout entry; nested `<Tab>` elements give you the top tab bar within that item.\n- `ContentTemplate` with `DataTemplate` defers page creation until navigated to.\n- `Routing.RegisterRoute` is needed for pages outside the Shell visual tree (like detail pages you push onto the navigation stack).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2ddb4781-41d5-42ab-9eb0-d7ddcd803c9c","outputTokens":623,"requestId":"980F:204067:16C51CA:1968770:6A0520EC"},"id":"becbbcdd-7d42-49cc-aa03-b5863e0e38e6","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:10:14.888Z","parentId":"011c8011-1c7f-497b-a3db-a1070ef09e18"}
